page.title: 12Our Dangerous Coast
page.content: The body of a child found at high water mark at Sennen Cove on Saturday is almost certainly that of one of the schoolboys from Stoke Poges, Bucking hamshire who were swept off rocks at Lands End,in early May. An inquest was due to open at Penzance on July 15th,on the four boys who were washed into the sea in the May tragedy The body of 11-years-old James Holloway was found some weeks ago.Also on Saturday the body of a woman,washed up at Nanjizal, has been identified as that of Mrs.Patricia Elizabeth Maunder,who went missing in May. Identity was confirmed on Tuesday by Penzance police.Mrs.Maunder had been missing from her home,and her car was found at Lands End on May 9.she had left a note in the vehicle. These trag edies make us, the children of Sennen very aware of our dangerous coast.
